An actress used as the Queen's body double for a London 2012 Olympics James Bond short film was required to show the director her ankles to ensure they were as good as Her Majesty's.

Julia McKenzie, 72, has revealed the unusual audition request was made after a director was concerned her legs wouldn't match the Queen's.

Most famous for playing Miss Marple, Mrs McKenzie filmed over several days at Buckingham Palace after the Queen volunteered to participate in the film herself.

