Asked why he was chosen for the jump, Mr Connery replied: 'Good question. I think they liked my legs.' He added: 'I’ve got Queen-style legs.'

Gary, who completed the world’s first skydive without a parachute in May 2012, said he had only one regret from the night: ‘I really wanted to keep the dress, but I wasn’t allowed. It would have looked great on a night out.’

The result was the most talked-about sequence of Danny Boyle’s stunning Olympics opening ceremony.

